From Outlook edit an email source or from Thunderbird insert html content( insert menu item in compose view) and add one of the following lines to a new email and send it to the account on the device:


<script type="text/javascript" >


function drawrectangle(){


var c=document.getElementById("myCanvas");


var ctx=c.getContext("2d");


ctx.fillStyle="#FF0000";


ctx.fillRect(0,0,150,75);


}


</script>


<canvas id="myCanvas" width="200" height="100"


style="border:1px solid #000000;">


</canvas> 


<div style="position:absolute; width:300px; height:300px;" 
onmousedown="drawrectangle();">Tap anywere</div>

